Description:
I have dynamic queue defined in a struct as
package mytest01;
    typedef struct {
        int b[$];
    } foo_t;

    function automatic foo_t bar();
        foo_t _foo;

        for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++) begin
            int tmp = $urandom();
            _foo.b.push_back(tmp);
        end
    endfunction // bar

endpackage

I got error while run verilator --cc mytest01.sv
%Error-UNSUPPORTED: mytest01.sv:11:20: Unsupported: Non-variable on LHS of built-in method 'push_back'
   11 |             _foo.b.push_back(tmp);
  |                    ^~~~~~~~~
                    ... For error description see https://verilator.org/warn/UNSUPPORTED?v=5.006
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.

If use temporary queue, there's no errors
package mytest02;
    typedef struct {
        int b[$];
    } foo_t;

    function automatic foo_t bar();
        foo_t _foo;
        int _b[$];

        for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++) begin
            int tmp = $urandom();
            _b.push_back(tmp);
        end
        _foo.b = _b;
    endfunction // bar

endpackage
